# Neural + AZL Orchestrated Model Training Pipeline

## System Architecture Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[AZL Program] --> B[Parser]
    B --> C[AST Nodes]
    C --> D[Interpreter]
    
    D --> E{Statement Type}
    E -->|Model Declaration| F[NeuralEngine.register_model]
    E -->|Train Command| G[NeuralEngine.train]
    E -->|Eval Command| H[NeuralEngine.eval]
    
    F --> I[Model Registry]
    G --> J[Training Loop]
    H --> K[Evaluation Engine]
    
    J --> L[ExecutionTrace]
    K --> M[ExecutionTrace]
    
    L --> N[ReflectionEngine]
    M --> O{Threshold Check}
    
    O -->|Success| P[Model Promoted]
    O -->|Failure| Q[Thought Queue]
    
    N --> R[ScoreVector Analysis]
    Q --> S[Reflection Trigger]
    
    R --> T[Adaptive Strategy]
    S --> U[Goal Rerouting]
    
    T --> V[Model Evolution]
    U --> W[Strategy Adjustment]
    
    V --> X[Improved Model]
    W --> Y[New Training Config]
    
    X --> Z[Next Training Cycle]
    Y --> Z
```

## AZL Grammar Specification

### Model Declaration
```azl
model "model_name" {
    input(dimensions),
    linear(input_dim, output_dim),
    relu(),
    linear(hidden_dim, output_dim),
    softmax()
}
```

### Training Command
```azl
train "model_name" with {
    loss: "crossentropy",
    optimizer: "adam", 
    epochs: 10
}
```

### Evaluation Command
```azl
eval "model_name" when accuracy < 0.9 {
    reflect("optimize_model")
}
```

## AST Structure

### ModelDeclaration
```rust
pub struct ModelDeclaration {
    pub name: String,
    pub layers: Vec<LayerSpec>,
}
```

### LayerSpec
```rust
pub struct LayerSpec {
    pub kind: LayerType,
    pub params: Vec<Expression>,
}
```

### TrainCommand
```rust
pub struct TrainCommand {
    pub model_name: String,
    pub loss: String,
    pub optimizer: String,
    pub epochs: u32,
}
```

### EvalCommand
```rust
pub struct EvalCommand {
    pub model_name: String,
    pub metric: String,
    pub threshold: f64,
    pub on_fail: Option<String>,
}
```

## Runtime Engine Functions

### NeuralEngine Core Methods
- `register_model(decl: &ModelDeclaration)` - Register new model architecture
- `train(config: &TrainCommand) -> ExecutionTrace` - Execute training loop
- `eval(config: &EvalCommand) -> ExecutionTrace` - Evaluate model performance
- `get_model_stats(name: &str) -> Option<(f64, f64)>` - Get accuracy/loss
- `list_models() -> Vec<String>` - List all registered models

### Integration Points
- **ReflectionEngine**: Training traces trigger self-evaluation
- **ThoughtQueue**: Failed evaluations add thoughts for retraining
- **ScoreVector**: Multi-dimensional performance analysis
- **ExecutionTrace**: Comprehensive training/evaluation metrics

## Training Flow Details

### 1. Model Registration
```rust
// AZL declares model architecture
model "mnist_classifier" {
    input(784),
    linear(784, 128),
    relu(),
    linear(128, 10),
    softmax()
}

// Rust runtime registers model
NeuralEngine::register_model(&declaration)
```

### 2. Training Execution
```rust
// AZL initiates training
train "mnist_classifier" with {
    loss: "crossentropy",
    optimizer: "adam",
    epochs: 10
}

// Rust executes training loop
let trace = NeuralEngine::train(&config)
```

### 3. Evaluation & Reflection
```rust
// AZL evaluates performance
eval "mnist_classifier" when accuracy < 0.9 {
    reflect("optimize_architecture")
}

// Rust evaluates and triggers reflection
let trace = NeuralEngine::eval(&config)
if trace.success_rate < threshold {
    ThoughtQueue::add("optimize_architecture")
}
```

